This is a game.  People want to logon and have fun, Verant's forgotten that in their "vision."  Instead of letting ubers die, and using their resources to develop new challeneges or needed fixes, they patch useless shit, that effect 5% of the uber-player base week-after-week.  The example I stated in the opening post (/gems) is the most glaring example.<br>
<br>
If Verant doesn't care about the uber-gamers, why do they spend SO much of their resources twinking that portion of the game?  The reason they care, is the uber-guilds are the rest of their audience 6-9 months down the road.</td></tr></table><br><p>[ No Comments Allowed for Anonymous, please <a href="user.php">register</a>  | <a href="comments.php?sid=111&pid=0&mode=&order=&thold=">Parent</a> ]</font><p><ul><li><a href="comments.php?op=showreply&tid=657&sid=111&pid=616&mode=&order=&thold=#657">Re: You're missing the point.</a> by Anonymous <font size=2>on Monday, March 05 @ 02:12:18 EST</font><br><ul><li><a href="comments.php?op=showreply&tid=666&sid=111&pid=657&mode=&order=&thold=#666">Re: You're missing the point.</a> by Anonymous <font size=2>on Monday, March 05 @ 10:06:10 EST</font><br></ul></ul></p><a name="1037"></a><table width=99% border=0><tr bgcolor="#efefef"><td width=500><p><b>Re: Regarding Furor and FoH's future in EverQuest.</b> <font size=2>(Score: 0)<br>by Anonymous on Friday, March 09 @ 20:05:03 EST</font></td></tr><tr><td>YES! we must stike at what's week!</td></tr></table><br><p>[ No Comments Allowed for Anonymous, please <a href="user.php">register</a>  | <a href="comments.php?sid=111&pid=0&mode=&order=&thold=">Parent</a> ]</font><p></ul></p></td><td bgcolor=ffffff><img src=themes/NukeNews/pixel.gif width=10 height=1 border=0></td></tr></table>

